items.text:
### Exciting Cast & Crew Call for Indie Short Film Sequel!

Hello all,

I'm thrilled to announce that my screenplay is nearly complete for an indie short filmâ€”a direct sequel to my concept piece, *"The Hollow Concept Short"* (check it out here: ([https://youtu.be/bVQf2tCT-z8?si=XUx23izsqJWtl-xT)](https://youtu.be/bVQf2tCT-z8?si=XUx23izsqJWtl-xT))). 

This upcoming story dives deep into the aftermath of 'The Hollow,' exploring its haunting progression into our modern world. If you love psychological thrillers with a conceptual twist, this is your chance to be part of something creative and impactful!

This is a **passion-driven, collaborative project** designed as a learning experience for everyone involved. As an indie production, all funds are dedicated towards film gear and post-productionâ€”no salaries, but tons of fun, skill-building, and networking opportunities!

**What We Offer:**

- Lunch on shoot days, a copy of the film and credits

- Hands-on experience in a creative environment

**We're Seeking VOLUNTEER TALENT ONLYâ€”Unpaid Roles:**

**Lead Actors (Auditions Required):**

- **Male Lead (Husband Role):** Caucasian, 30-35 years old, slim/athletic build. Must convey emotion, and intensity. This is a starring role with significant screen time!

- **Female Lead (Wife Role):** Caucasian, 29-32 years old, slim/athletic build. Static character, convey emotion and depth with the male leadâ€”bring your A-game!

*First-time actors are absolutely welcome!* We'll hold tryouts online and discuss roles in detail to ensure the best fit. No prior experience? No problemâ€”we're all about promoting growth!

**How to Apply for Acting Roles:**

- Send a wide-shot full-body photo + a close-up headshot.

- Include any reels, clips, or acting samples if available (not required).

- Email applications to [reddybry8films@gmail.com](mailto:reddybry8films@gmail.com) with the subject: "Actor Application - [Role] - [Your Name]".

- Tell us a bit about yourself and why you're excited about this project!

**Supporting Roles & Crew:** 1 PA to help with camera & crew, few minor parts are still in developmentâ€”stay tuned for updates, or express interest in your application if you're open to flexibility.

Filming will take place in the Toronto area, with flexible scheduling to accommodate volunteers. Date: tbd, Filming to be done <Dec13

Let's create something memorable togetherâ€”apply today and join the journey!

Questions? Reach out via email. Looking forward to your submissions!

Best,  

Bharad Reddy

Writer/Director/Editor

@reddybry8films

Male actor, 25-40 years old, wanted.

You should be good-looking and well-built and not afraid of queer parts.

I'm an actor from Germany and from time to time I also make short films, which I present at international film festivals .

My films are arthouse films that may contain nudity and improvisation.

My upcoming short will be an online romance.

The actor should therefore record their part at home using their own smartphone.

Unfortunately, there's no payment, but it only takes 1-2 days. Sorry,  It's not possible to make money with a short film.
Filming will be in English.

I'm also looking for actors for potential future projects.

This is me: www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928

Please write to Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de

CASTING CALL FOR SHORT FILM (SPLENDOR) TO BE SHOT THIS WEEKEND, 8TH AND 9TH OF NOVEMBER | LONDON | RICHMOND PARK

TRAVEL AND EXPENSES COVERED

PAID

SYNOPSIS
An elderly dying blind poet and her violinist granddaughter she raised, go on a last trip to a spot where she was truly alive during her youth. Unknowingly, the journey will become an absolute metamorphosis for both.

Roles

**GRANDDAUGHTER AGE 19-25: A violinist and emerging poet who was adopted by her grandmother after the absence of her parents. She has a clinging bond with her grandmother and inwardly refuses to let go of her grandmother.**

**Grandmother AGE 55-80: A poet who has lost her sight and has stopped writing. She adopted her granddaughter, and the sound of her violin is the only thing that gives her joy. She wants to travel one last time to a nature spot where she felt most alive during her youth.**

(not obligatory but preferable with a fine art performance background)

CONTACT:

Instragram [@___reincarnated](https://www.instagram.com/___reincarnated/?hl=es)

**e-mail: K2554905@kingston.ac.uk**

sharedPost.text:
Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 45/2025

KINDERKINO IM DORF UND GEDENKEN AN EINEN GROSSEN DEUTSCHEN KOMPONISTEN

Von der Kritik gefeiert startet jetzt der hochgelobte Film IN DIE SONNE SCHAUEN in den Kinos und durften so nebenbei mit Darstellerin Lena Urzendowsky ein paar Worte wechseln.

Ein weiteres Kapitel der Sify Saga schlÃ¤gt PREDATOR: BADLANDS auf, und zwar in einigen unserer Kooperationskinos. Ob der Film was taugt oder nicht, erzÃ¤hlt Ihnen unsere Filmexpertin in der Sendung.

Vor kurzem fand in Sonnberg mit der Romanverfilmung HEIDI (2015) das erste Kinderkino in kleinen Orten statt. Wir baten die Organisatorin und Mitarbeiterin der KulturmÃ¼ Hollabrunn, Roswitha Bauda, um ein Interview. 

Weitere Filmtipps und Musik zu Ehren des kÃ¼rzlich verstorbenen Klaus Doldinger prÃ¤sentiert Ihnen Sarah Fuchs.

Mittwoch 5.11.25 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

Union / Non-Union: Non-Union
Production Type: Independent
Project length: Short film
Project format: 4:3
Production Company: JMA FILMS 
Director: Justin Adams
Audition Location: Video Audition
Shooting Location:  Wrightsville PA
Email: Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com
Compensation: Unpaid. Food and IMDb credit only.

Synopsis: A boy won't finish his milk and so the babysitter tells him a story about a not so kind milkman

Casting information: PLEASE READ 
Character Bios:

WOMAN(Support Character) Female 30-35. in the flashback scene from the 50's

To be considered, you MUST send your CV/Resume to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com. Do not use messenger. If you DO NOT reside in the DMV or York PA areas, we will not look at your submission unless you state you are willing to travel/lodge at your own expense. All actors will provide their own transportation.

The audition process:
1. Submit a resume or CV along with a head shot to Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com
2. Please state in the subject line the name of the character.
3. If selected, you will be given sides, instructions on how to submit, and a due date.
Any questions can be sent to the Filmmakerjustin@gmail.com email.

CASTING CALL FOR SHORT FILM TO BE SHOT THIS WEEKEND, 8TH AND 9TH OF NOVEMBER | LONDON | RICHMOND PARK

TRAVEL AND EXPENSES COVERED

PAID

An elder poet who is losing her sight and her violinist granddaughter go on a journey to the grandmotherâ€™s birthplace - a cabin in the woods - where she will reconnect with life itself.

Roles

GRANDDAUGHTER AGE 19-25: A violinist and emerging poet who was adopted by her grandmother after the absence of her parents. She has a clinging bond with her grandmother and inwardly refuses to let go of her grandfather.

GRANDFATHER AGE 60-80: A poet who has lost his sight and has stopped writing. He adopted her granddaughter, and the sound of her violin is the only thing that gives him joy. He wants to travel one last time to a nature spot where he felt most alive during his youth.
(not obligatory but preferable with a fine art performance background)

CONTACT:

Instragram [@___reincarnated](https://www.instagram.com/___reincarnated/?hl=es)

**e-mail: K2554905@kingston.ac.uk**

Open Call In Person Auditions Mon. & Tues. Nov 10 & 11 at 7pm for The 39 Steps by Patrick Barlow, Directed by Liz Bove. Performances: Jan. 9-18: Fri. & Sat. 8pm & Sundays 2pm + 2pm Matinee Sat. 1/17. More Details @ [https://www.facebook.com/share/17ZdspnYwH/](https://www.facebook.com/share/17ZdspnYwH/) Auditions @HeightsPlayers 26 Willow Place Brooklyn, NY 11201. (718) 237-2752. Please bring a headshot and resume, sides available on website. Please be sure to be available for in person call backs. NO pay.

CHARACTER BREAKDOWN:

**A familiarity with the Hitchcock film, The 39 Steps (1935), is highly recommended as the play is a direct spoof on the film. You may find this on ****[Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jfVtoPN3BVk)****.**
**Richard Hannay:** 30s-40s. A Hitchcock-esque suave, dashing, debonaire fellow. A physically adept comedian. Must be able to do a British accent. 

**Annabella Schmidt:** 20s-30s. An exotic and intriguing spy. Must be able to do a German accent. Actress will also play Margaret. 

**Pamela**: 20s-30s. The quintessential Hitchcock-esqe leading lady. She is bold, emotionally and intellectually intelligent. British accent required. 

**Margaret**: 20s-30s. The wife of a stern religious Scottish farmer. Scottish accent required. Actress will also play Annabella. 

**Clown #1 **& **Clown #2:** Any age, gender, race. Vivacious and debonair, both clowns expertly execute multiple male and female roles with skillful physical comedic skills.  English and Scottish accents a must.

â€œStep into the shadows for an unforgettable night of darkly dazzling musical theater. This brand-new cabaret dives into the thrilling worlds of Lizzie: The Rock Musical, The Addams Family, Bat Boy: The Musical, and Sweeney Todd. Featuring a killer cast of powerhouse voices, the evening will blend rock energy, wicked humor, and hauntingly beautiful melodies in a celebration of the darker side of Broadway. Conceived and directed by Gabrielle Dillinger, this electrifying concert invites audiences to embrace the strange, the spooky, and the spectacular. Come experience a night thatâ€™s deliciously twisted and devilishly fun.â€

All auditions due November 27th @11:59PM, with us getting in touch on November 30th.

items.text:
TALENT NEEDED for Music Video!

**Date:** Saturday, December 13th

**Location**: Victorian mansion in Altadena, CA

**Rate**: $100/day (non-union): $100/day (non-union)

**Experience**: On-camera experience preferred, but not required

**Deadline**: Tuesday, November 11th at 11:59pm

**Additional**: Credit on distribution platforms and end-credits, BTS content, and permission to use in portfolios

These are supporting roles with lots of screen time (no dialogue) that will portray eerie, cult-like personalities.

**SISTERS 1 & 2**: Age 18-28 to play two sisters to the Lead character, helping prepare her for a coming-of-age cult-like ceremony. Preferably appearing Slavic, with blond hair, fair skin, and blue/green eyes.

**FATHER**: Age 35-60 to play the Leadâ€™s father as the dominant head-of-house, facilitating a generational coming-of-age cult-like ceremony. Preferably appearing Slavic, with blond or gray hair, fair skin, and blue/green eyes.

**GRANDMOTHER**: Age 60+ to play the leadâ€™s grandmother, weathered by constricting traditional values, bitterly upholding traditionally gendered expectations of home-keeper, preparing the Lead for a coming-of-age cult-like ceremony. Preferably appearing Slavic, with gray hair, fair skin, and blue/green eyes. This role will consist of a scene scrubbing the Lead in a bathtub (explicit body parts covered) as if washing away her sins.

If interested, please email [hailey@eaton-media.com](mailto:hailey@eaton-media.com);
* First and last name
* A headshot/photo of yourself
* Age
* Resume/portfolio (Please note if you donâ€™t have one)
* Your availability for Saturday, December 13th

**The Revolution of Independent Film Starts Here.**

This Christmas at Lower Drayton Farm we are looking for experienced performers in our Jingle Ville. We are looking for joyful Elves, a friendly Mrs Claus and of course a Magical Santa. 

Our Santa's grotto experience is like no other and we need you guys to come down and help bring the magic to life. Not only will our customers be able to come and visit Santa they will also get the chance to meet Mrs Claus, watch a Lower Drayton Farm christmas film, have lots of fun doing activities with the Elves and much more! 

The Christmas period will be from the 22nd November to 24th December at Play@ Lower Drayton Farm in Penkridge. 

If interested please email play@lowerdraytonfarm.co.uk. Please include your CV, headshot and role you are applying for. We can't wait to hear from you soon!

Casting Brief

We are casting a drama scene that plays out in a VR training environment for security service industry personnel. This is a high drama realistic video, where you interact directly with the audience, looking into the lens, in the same way as in PeepShow.  Please read the casting breakdowns and only apply if you meet the requirements and are available on that shoot date. Please do not apply if youâ€™re not. Full details on the application below.  We can't repsond to "interested". Please follow the details below. Thanks in advance.

Shoot Date: 19th November.  (locked no deviation on the date)

Shoot Times: Approx 8am - 7pm

Location:    Romford

Nearest Tube: Chadwell Heath (Elizabeth line)

Rick - Male 25-45 Any Ethnicity  - Security officer - calm and organised. Working security at high profile events. Someone who can be relied on. Professional look. Interacting with the lead

Steve  - Male 25-45 Any Ethnicity Security officer - lazy uninterested in taking things overly seriously. Does the bare minimum. Smart look overall. Interacting with the lead

Commander Alan - Male 35-50 Any Ethnicity - ex military type. Knows the seriousness of the job and what it takes to keep people safe. Interacting with the lead

Kelly - Female 24-35 Any Ethnicity - guest at the event, is involved in a high stress situation when during an attack she is separate from a loved one. Interacting with the lead

Stef - Female  25-45 Any Ethnicity - guest at the event, is involved in a high stress situation when during an attack she is separate from a loved one. Interacting with the lead

Ali - Waiter / waitress / host  Male / Female  25-45 Any Ethnicity - high end service industry professional working hard in the venue. Gets caught up in a high stress situation and tries to get past / around the lead

Danny - Photographer  Male / Female 25-45 a photographer with kit who is pushy about gaining access to certain areas, with or without rules being broken. Interacting with the lead

X - Male / Female 25-45 - this person is either a red herring or a criminal. Could they be doing something wrong, or just in the wrong place?  Interacting with the lead

The singer  - Male / Female 25-45 Any Ethnicity - performing on the main stage, solo gig to the audience, itâ€™s your concert, your gig. Will be lip syncing to a couple of tracks while the experience plays out.

To apply please send an email with Subject Title â€œAudition T19 (and include the roleâ€ eg  Audition T19 Danny

Please send a brief email stating your experience and why you're suited to the role. 

Please include a recent headshot and full length.

Please include a youtube link to your showreel, if you donâ€™t have a showreel a link to a brief monologue with an intro to who you are.

Please send submissions to info@ultrareality.co.uk

Paid: Â£175

Use: private online in training app only. Not public.

Credits will be given

items.text:
### Exciting Cast & Crew Call for Indie Short Film Sequel!

Hello all,

I'm thrilled to announce that my screenplay is nearly complete for an indie short filmâ€”a direct sequel to my concept piece, *"The Hollow Concept Short"* (check it out here: ([https://youtu.be/bVQf2tCT-z8?si=XUx23izsqJWtl-xT)](https://youtu.be/bVQf2tCT-z8?si=XUx23izsqJWtl-xT))). 

This upcoming story dives deep into the aftermath of 'The Hollow,' exploring its haunting progression into our modern world. If you love psychological thrillers with a conceptual twist, this is your chance to be part of something creative and impactful!

This is a **passion-driven, collaborative project** designed as a learning experience for everyone involved. As an indie production, all funds are dedicated towards film gear and post-productionâ€”no salaries, but tons of fun, skill-building, and networking opportunities!

**What We Offer:**

- Lunch on shoot days, a copy of the film and credits

- Hands-on experience in a creative environment

**We're Seeking VOLUNTEER TALENT ONLYâ€”Unpaid Roles:**

**Lead Actors (Auditions Required):**

- **Male Lead (Husband Role):** Caucasian, 30-35 years old, slim/athletic build. Must convey emotion, and intensity. This is a starring role with significant screen time!

- **Female Lead (Wife Role):** Caucasian, 29-32 years old, slim/athletic build. Static character, convey emotion and depth with the male leadâ€”bring your A-game!

*First-time actors are absolutely welcome!* We'll hold tryouts online and discuss roles in detail to ensure the best fit. No prior experience? No problemâ€”we're all about promoting growth!

**How to Apply for Acting Roles:**

- Send a wide-shot full-body photo + a close-up headshot.

- Include any reels, clips, or acting samples if available (not required).

- Email applications to [reddybry8films@gmail.com](mailto:reddybry8films@gmail.com) with the subject: "Actor Application - [Role] - [Your Name]".

- Tell us a bit about yourself and why you're excited about this project!

**Supporting Roles & Crew:** 1 PA to help with camera & crew, few minor parts are still in developmentâ€”stay tuned for updates, or express interest in your application if you're open to flexibility.

Filming will take place in the Toronto area, with flexible scheduling to accommodate volunteers. Date: tbd, Filming to be done <Dec13

Let's create something memorable togetherâ€”apply today and join the journey!

Questions? Reach out via email. Looking forward to your submissions!

Best,  

Bharad Reddy

Writer/Director/Editor

@reddybry8films

topComments.text: Unless it's a student film always pay your cast and crew. Copy, credit and last weeks moldy pizza is not any kind of "offer". You get copy credit and real food on paying jobs so you're not "offering" anything special

Tripple D Agency

Hi!

NB: Cape Town based. 

We looking for comfortable mother's of all ages who have lost their child in a road accident to share their stories.
This is not an acting role but for real stories to be shared by real mom's. This Casting call will help prevent future tragedies and encourage responsible driving across.

Shoot date : 19 November 2025.
Around Cape Town.

If you're who we looking for or know someone that might fit this brief please WhatsApp us your full name and age to 0731078818.
I'll then send Casting instructions. 

Please note you need to be comfortable in sharing your story.

Submission deadline :Saturday 9th November.

Howdy Denver film community! Weâ€™re Wasteland of Wonder, a boutique film production company based here in Denver, CO that focuses on community building through creative collaboration. Weâ€™re seeking an actor for a music video and would love to engage with some new, local talent. Email us at wastelandofwonder@gmail.com for information about auditions!

TITLE: â€œDonâ€™t Thinkâ€ 

GENRE: Gothic industrial music video 

SYNOPSIS: â€œDonâ€™t Thinkâ€ explores themes of control and alienation both societally and personally with evocative and surreal imagery.  Our protagonist, Ezra, is an audience member at a surrealist concert- who slowly loses themself in the music. In a B plot we see manufacturers, men in a unique blend of industrial and medical garb, grooming and preparing Ezra for some kind of operation.  

CHARACTER: Ezra, (20s), feels alienated and unable to connect with others.  Ezraâ€™s arc in the video is one of surrender and vulnerability, giving in to the pressures of everyone around them. 

This role is open casting for Men and Nonbinary actors of any race. Ideally the actor would be very skilled in physical work and have a dramatic background. 

PRODUCTION INFO

PRODUCTION COMPANY: Wasteland of Wonder (wastelandofwonder.com)

PRODUCTION TYPE: Music Video

CONTACT INFO: wastelandofwonder@gmail.com

COMPENSATION: The role will be compensated, rate TBD 

AUDITION INFORMATION: No audition, just send us a resume and reel :). Email us for further information. 

SHOOT SCHEDULE: Mid November 

FILMING LOCATION: Denver Metro & the Front Range

CASTING CALL: Protesters Voiceover â€“ â€œDenied Careâ€ Series

Project Title: Denied Care
Production Company: Superstar TV Entertainment, Inc.
Type: Voiceover (Non-Union / Indie Production)
Location: Remote Recording Accepted
Compensation: paid 
Recording Date: November 15th

Looking for 3 voiceovers

---

PROJECT OVERVIEW

Denied Care is a scripted drama following Ava Winters, a young woman denied life-saving treatment by a broken healthcare system. The story exposes the real human cost of bureaucratic neglect through emotional, defiant, and darkly comedic storytelling.

Short Film feature a pivotal protest montage â€” where voices from across the nation rise in solidarity. This casting call is for those protester voices â€” raw, real, and unapologetic.

---

ROLE: PROTESTER VOICEOVER (MULTIPLE TALENTS)

Gender: Any
Age Range: 18â€“65
Accent: Open â€” diverse voices encouraged
Tone: Authentic, passionate, emotional, and real
Vocal Quality:

Gritty, tired, but determined

Feels like youâ€™ve lived it â€” not â€œperformedâ€ it

Think real activists, not voice actors

Examples of Lines (for audition):

â€œWe are not invisible!â€

â€œYou canâ€™t deny care to the living!â€

â€œWeâ€™re sick, not silent!â€

â€œEvery denial has a name!â€

â€œWe are the denied â€” and weâ€™re not backing down!â€

(Actors may be asked to record crowd-style chants, overlapping dialogue, and emotional reactions.)

---

RECORDING NOTES

Please record clean audio (WAV or MP3) with minimal background noise.

Multiple takes with varying energy levels are encouraged.

Shouting, chanting, and overlapping crowd energy welcome.

Casting Call: Singer-Songwriter for Music Video (Unpaid)

Production Title: Christmas Music video 
Production Company: Superstar TV Entertainment Inc.
Type: Music Video
Location: Colorado (exact location TBD)

Compensation: Unpaid (Copy, Credit, and Meals Provided)

---

About the Project

Superstar TV Entertainment Inc. is producing a heartfelt, cinematic music video featuring a singer-songwriter whose performance captures raw emotion and authenticity. This project is designed to highlight both the artist and visual storytelling â€” similar in tone to Lewis Capaldi, Adele, or Noah Kahan.

The final video will be professionally shot and released across Superstar TV platforms, YouTube, and social media for maximum exposure.

---

Roles

ðŸŽ¤ Lead Artist / Singer-Songwriter (Principal Role)

Requirements: Must be reliable, punctual, and open to creative collaboration.

This Christmas at Lower Drayton Farm we are looking for experienced performers in our Jingle Ville. We are looking for joyful Elves, a friendly Mrs Claus and of course a Magical Santa. 

Our Santas grotto experience is like no other and we need you guys to come down and help bring the magic to life. Not only will our customers be able to come and visit Santa they will also get the chance to meet Mrs Claus, watch a Lower Drayton Farm christmas film, have lots of fun doing activities with the Elves and much more! 

The Christmas period will be from the November to 24th December at Play@ Lower Drayton Farm in Penkridge. 

If interested please email play@lowerdraytonfarm.co.uk. Please include your CV, headshot and role you are applying for. We can't wait to hear from you soon!

items.text:
Casting call, crew and actors.
Proof of concept scene/short film
Northwest based, filming at Chester castle 

Hi all, I'm currently recruiting for film crew and actors. This is for a proof of concept scene. The scene itself is a secret meeting that takes place between King Henry VIII and Anne Boleyn on the night before her execution. A great location and has already been sourced, a chapel in a castle. 

This is a passion project, but I may be able to stretch my budget to cover travel, and food and drinks will all definitely be provided.

 Based on if the proof of concept is succ#essful, all cast and crew will get a percentage of the profits and have guaranteed paid jobs and roles in the main feature. 

Please message me for further details on recruitment and casting. I aim to shoot this in the first half of 2026.

Looking for several make actors of all ages to play guards in the tower, small speaking parts.

Actress who can play aged 30 to 45, to play role of Anne Boleyn's guardian. Small speaking role.

Anne Boleyn- actress who can play aged range 28 to 36

Camera crew, sound crew and editors also wanted. 

Thank you

EXTRAS NEEDED for Music Video!

Filming date: Sunday, December 14th

Filming location: Victorian mansion in Altadena, CA

Experience: On-camera experience is preferred, but not required

Deadline: Tuesday, November 11th at 11:59pm

Compensation: this is a low-budget non-union production, so these are unpaid roles. We will be able to provide meals, snacks, credit on distribution platforms and end-credits, BTS content, and permission to use in portfolios.

These are roles with lots of screen time (no dialogue) that will portray party-goers, rock band audience, and rowdy underground fight spectators (super fun stuff planned!)

If interested, please email [hailey@eaton-media.com](mailto:hailey@eaton-media.com);
* First and last name
* A headshot/photo of yourself
* Age
* Resume/portfolio (if you have one, please note if you donâ€™t)
* Your availability for Sunday, December 14th.

I look forward to hearing from you!

sharedPost.text:
***SAFEGUARDING ALERT - CHILDREN ON SOCIAL MEDIA***

PARENTS AND AGENTS - please read carefully. This incident highlights the dangers of children using social media and the importance of exercising due care should you choose to allow your child to have a presence on these platforms: 

One of our member agents was informed of an incident that occurred in a West End Theatre. They were informed of a safeguarding risk on a production one of their clients are in.  

A person with a criminal record for online grooming was able to make contact to child accounts from the production, due to active and public accounts in a child's name on Instagram.

The contact seemed friendly, but we know from their previous that this is a repeated pattern of behaviour to get access with unlawful intentions.

The contact progressed from online to Stage Door where a chaperone intercepted the interaction.

The production is very clear that active, public and taggable accounts are not allowed for the duration of their contract, this includes accounts that are â€˜parent runâ€™. This risk came as a direct consequence of not following these rules and engaging with unknown accounts on social media.

The rules, which are part of the contract, are there for a reason and this is why they should not be breached at any time.

The theatre immediately recognised the red flags and acted promptly to ensure that all children were kept safe.

 

Our Best Practice Document for Children on Social Media is linked here

https://www.theaypa.co.uk/bestpractisedocs
